"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering resource access in native image**\\n\\nI realize that the resource is located in the library JAR, and `Class#getResourceAsStream` can read class bytes when running on the JVM. For the native image, class resources might also be included by the agent since the agent records what is accessed during tests. I’m wondering if `Class#getResourceAsStream` can access the class byte resource in the native image. It seems possible if the resource configuration is generated correctly.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering next steps**\\n\\nI think I need to check existing resources, but I'm not entirely sure if it's necessary. I don’t think I need to run tests at this point. However, I need to make sure to commit my work. Before I dive into coding, I should search for information about the webserver to ensure I have everything I need. It’s good to be thorough before moving forward!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_51J4OFS2YGt1oWlhqlOz5fgd|fc_078a37d0418c78800169ef54001e84819194b5aede840122d7", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "rg \"Webserver\" tests/src/org.javassist/javassist/3.24.1-GA/src/test/java /home/vjovanov/c/forge4/metadata-forge/local_repositories/source_context/org.javassist/javassist/3.24.1-GA/main/extracted -g '*.java'", "timeout": 10}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1000, "output": 869, "cacheRead": 14848, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 16717, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777292272917, "responseId": "resp_078a37d0418c78800169ef53f13bf88191a1e62ec47e12a7b9"}}
